Text: Looks very interesting. Great collection, wee.
I get an error message when I try to start this torrent. It's because you are not supposed to use : in filename! But thanx anyway.
Sorry, in linux a : in a filename works just fine so didn't think of how windows would handle it..:) Though it worked to download i guess?

Windows users, you can get it with the command line.  This was my command for bittornado: 

btdownloadgui --saveas npws.avi --max_upload_rate 13 e:npws.torrent

The client already kept all my previous settings from before; and specifying the download name avoids the dialog that crashes.

COrrection, that should be .pdf.
 wee, thanks for the upload.
